{"TopicId":147135,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"Check if SmartA.S.S. is active","CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T18:39:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T18:39:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need the piece of code to check if SmartASS on a given Vessel is set to anything but off. Also I\u0027d like to handle the case that MechJeb is not installed at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anybody know how to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MOARdV","CreatedById":60950,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-06T01:41:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222743131\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473100760\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anybody know how to?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be more helpful: are you using reflection, or are you hard-linking to the MechJeb DLL? \u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/MOARdV/AvionicsSystems/blob/master/Source/MASIMechJeb.cs#L850\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis method\u003C/a\u003E takes advantage of reflection to set up a delegate that checks if SmartASS is off. \u00A0If you hard-link, you will do just about the same thing, only you won\u0027t need reflection to get to the methods and field you need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-06T05:26:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/60950-moardv/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002260950\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/60950-moardv/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MOARdV\u003C/a\u003E, you\u0027re my hero! :\u0027-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, I wanted to use reflection. I just didn\u0027t know how to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-06T05:27:12Z\u0022 title=\u002209/06/2016 05:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 6, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by MarkusA380\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}